==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trochlear
<hw>Troch"le*ar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trochlea</ets> block or pulley.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Shaped like, or resembling, a pulley; pertaining to, or connected
with, a trochlea; <as>as, a <ex>trochlear</ex> articular surface; the
<ex>trochlear</ex> muscle of the eye.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Trochlear nerve</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Pathetic
nerve</cref>, under <er>Pathetic</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trochleary</ent>⟦br⟧
